<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="539" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d539">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/279: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Lay</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-07T14:00:00-06:00">March 7, 1934—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:12 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>22. My telegram No. 20, March 6, 6 p.m. Honduran Minister for Foreign
                            Affairs now tells me that Honduran Government now agrees with Nicaragua,
                            Salvador, and Guatemala to hold Conference on March 15 as originally
                            planned, and that Honduran delegates will be appointed tomorrow.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Central American missions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lay</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>